    `components/IndiaMap.tsx`

## 3. Usage in a Page
Since your project uses the **App Router** (`app` folder), you can import it directly into any page (e.g., `app/page.tsx` or `app/about/page.tsx`).

```tsx
import IndiaMap from '@/components/IndiaMap'; 

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <main className="flex flex-col items-center justify-between p-24">
      
      <div className="w-full h-[600px] relative">
        <IndiaMap className="rounded-lg shadow-lg" />
      </div>

    </main>
  );
}
```

## Key Features for Your Stack
- **TypeScript ([.tsx](file:///C:/Users/Manish/.gemini/antigravity/brain/7fe4f053-2427-4eaf-9ea8-b77cd2073e47/IndiaMap.tsx))**: Fully typed and compatible with your `tsconfig.json`.
- **Tailwind Ready**: The component accepts `className`, so you can style the container (e.g., `h-[500px] w-full`) using standard Tailwind classes.
- **Client Side**: Uses `'use client'` automatically to work within the Next.js Server Components architecture.
